column5: Thanks for the mental diversion lads!!!  Too bad Phil was a no show..whimp! Afraid to be outdone??
Good thing it wan't an ugly face competition. I would have won hands down.   What was the prize???
Phil's got NOTHING on that shirt Wayne.  That is the worst one I have and it looks to be the most tame too.
Yes Wayne you win that shirt is damn ugly!!!
Ugly... Some of those shirts are the same as my Sunday bests I put on when we go to church and walmart...
We have a winna.......  Yup, that's gotta be the ugliest shirt I've seen in a long time Wayne

Leah and I almost got thrown out of Value Village at Bloor and Lansdowne buying our shirts! Laughing so hard, I was in the mens section and she headed over to wimmins. I was holding up shirts and yelling over.. "what about this one, ugly enough?"
stylin'

You guys would be a HIT at a Beach Boy's Concert.   1st prize for sure I guess I better clean my closet out, my wife has been on me for years. So you guys think my shirts are funny. You hurt my feelings  I love those shirts, only to go back to the days. 50's & 60's
So ugly she had to keep her eyes closed.
Future wife repellents for sure.
That's just sad.....  But to be honest I've seen HH in that shirt before, it's everyday wear.

OH MAN!!!!!  That is hilarious!  Love the Woody Joe, VINTAGE!  Wayne, what a score, just amazing (Can I borrow it?)  GBW, looks like a camo hunting shirt, LOVE IT!  Leah, I actually have the same shirt, great taste girlfriend!  I'm sorry I had to miss it.
you know what's real funny about that?  We all commented as to "what type of man would wear that one" as it is a mens med.  Now we know...
they are ugly
I can see (barely now after looking at those shirts) why you won Wayne. Care to join us for an ugly shirt day of fishing??

HA! The type of man that can drive a small car, doesn't need a ball sack hanging from his spare tire, wears pink dish gloves, cries watching Caddy shack or needs to use a 18ft rod on the rivers to make up for lack of something else.  But real reason, I could give a rat arse what others think.  Plus, I think its cool, but I think the same about my vintage trucker hats and Samantha Fox....
Hey, what ever happended to Samatha Fox... did she end up with mange? HH

In 2010, Fox teamed up with trance superstar 4 Strings to release a new single, "Forever". Summer 2010 saw the release of a duet with Italian singer Sabrina Salerno in which they performed a cover version of Blondie's hit "Call Me". Released in Italy on 15 June, the single peaked at #4 in the Italian Dance Singles Sales Chart on the first week of July.[3]  On 10 August 2010, The Beatles Complete On Ukulele released her reimagining of The Beatles' "I Should Have Known Better" featuring ukulele.[4]  from Wikipedia: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samantha_Fox
If I had a party, you would be the first on my list.
I bet if you sent that shirt to Ripleys Believe it or Not, they would send it back with a note saying "We just don't believe it Wayne"
I dunno Phil, a guy does not usually comment "Love the woody Joe" to another guy! LOL Just sayin.......
good catch RT
HA! Nice one!  I didn't even do that on purpose!
I'm not surprised, he has never complained before! HH
